### 6.1 Starting state (live, 2026-05-11)

- `structural_score = 80.3` (depth 0.60, freshness 0.485, hero 0.80, balance/density/sourcing maxed)
- `utility_score = TBD` — Rakon judges the live page on first tick; my eyeball estimate is 5.5–6.5/10 (well-structured + cited, but open questions buried as prose; debate-tagged claims = 0; JWST-era frontier weakly represented).
- `composite Q0 ≈ 0.35 * 0.80 + 0.65 * 0.60 = 0.67` (using my eyeball mid-point for utility).

### 6.2 Success criteria (composite-based)

| Window | Target |
|---|---|
| First experiment | One commit (proves drafter + judge + rollback path end-to-end) |
| 6 hours (~72 ticks) | `Q ≥ 0.72` (e.g. struct ≥84, util ≥6.5) AND ≥2 missing subtopics covered AND ≥2 debate-tagged claims added |
| 24 hours (~288 ticks) | `Q ≥ 0.78` AND struct ≥90 AND util ≥7.5 AND zero missing subtopics AND ≥4 debate claims AND freshness ≥0.70 |
| Voice check | Manual: page still reads as a research review article. No roadmap-card / compass-tile drift (Papa's standing wiki-voice feedback). |
| Judge calibration | Papa spot-reviews 5 random `judge_rationale` rows; agrees with the judge's direction (up/down) in ≥4 of 5. If not, prompt revision before continuing. |

### 6.3 First 5 experiments — concrete predictions (utility-aware)

