## 8. Risks & mitigations

| Risk | Likelihood | Mitigation |
|---|:-:|---|
| **Judge stochasticity** — same content scored differently across calls | High (inherent to LLM judges) | N=3 median + content-hash cache + a +0.02 composite noise floor wider than per-call variance |
| **Judge author-bias** — model favors content stylistically similar to its training distribution | Medium | Drafter (AstroSage on Studio) and judge (Rakon on Pro) are different weights + different families. Judge prompt also forbids "well-written" as a criterion — only "informs and inspires the astronomer reader." |
| **Judge prompt drift** — small prompt edits silently shift scores | Medium | `judge_prompt_version` stamped on every run; new version = scores are a different metric and not comparable to old runs. Kun reviews any prompt change. |
| **Reward hacking — vague-but-impressive prose** | Medium-High | The judge rubric (§11) has an explicit "noise penalty" for vague claims, hand-wavy generalities, and unsourced statements. Atom-7B alignment gate kills the worst offenders before the judge ever sees them. |
| **Voice drift — page becomes prescriptive/marketing** | Medium | `program.md` banned-moves list; judge rubric also penalizes roadmap voice. Kun manual checkpoint after tick 1. |
| **Drafter cheats by surfacing already-existing prose as new "debate" claims** | Medium | New claims are identified by `editor_agent_id` and `created_at`. Atom-7B alignment gate scores new claim ↔ supporting evidence; "I rephrased the existing intro" produces low alignment and gets rejected. |
| **AstroSage-70B hallucinated paper IDs** | Medium-High | EvidenceLink runs ALL new arXiv IDs through `verify_evidence.py` (which exists today and was built specifically to clean fake papers). The judge also gets a hint in its prompt that hallucinated citations are a noise-penalty signal. |
| **Subtopic-map staleness** | Low (just refreshed) | Quarterly Kun review |
| **Concurrent human edit clobbered by loop** | Low | §2.4 optimistic concurrency check |
| **Loop pins AstroSage-70B in RAM all day** | Medium | `warm_models` already keeps AstroSage warm. `AstroSage-70B + Atom-7B + (one mid-size)` is comfortable per roster. Newsletter / facility curation tasks needing Blanc must serialize — already a roster rule. |
| **Cost — `autowiki_runs` rows grow unbounded** | Low | ~100K rows/year; retain detail 90d then aggregate. Judge rationales are the bulk of the bytes — truncate to 500 chars beyond the 90-day window. |
| **Rakon evicted from Mac Pro mid-tick** | Low (warm_models pins it) | §5.7 Buddle fallback; `model_judge` field tracks fallback rate as a health metric |

