## Appendix A — Mapping autoresearch → autowiki

| autoresearch | autowiki v1.1 |
|---|---|
| `train.py` | `wiki_pages.content` + `claims` + `evidence` for one page |
| `val_bpb` (single number, lower=better) | `quality = 0.35·struct/100 + 0.65·utility/10` (single number, higher=better), composite of deterministic structural score + Rakon-judged astronomer utility |
| `program.md` (per-agent skill) | `autowiki/programs/<slug>.md` (per-page skill) + `prompts/judge_v1.md` (rubric prompt) |
| 5-min wall-clock budget | 5-min wall-clock tick, ~120-220s typical usage |
| Keep-if-better / discard-otherwise | `Δquality ≥ +0.02 AND struct didn't regress >0.5 AND no struct component dropped >0.05` |
| One agent | One drafter (AstroSage) + one judge (Rakon, different host + different weights) + Atom-7B alignment gate |
| Iteration log (val_bpb history) | `autowiki_runs` table with full judge rationale + raw sub-scores |
| Rollback = git revert | Rollback = `PageVersion` restore + delete rows tagged with `editor_agent_id` |
| Pure numerical metric | Composite metric — pure numbers are insufficient because page quality includes "would an astronomer be inspired to research further," which is irreducibly a judgment |
